{
    "level": "sentence",
    "abstract": [
        {
            "text": "Recent results on CP parameters of the B systems obtained by the CDF and D\u00d8 collaborations using the data samples collected at the Tevatron Collider in the period 2002 -2007 were presented at the QCD 2008 conference (Montpellier, France). ",
            "paragraph_rank": 0,
            "section_rank": 1
        },
        {
            "text": "These results include measurements of the mixing phase \u03c6 J/\u03c8\u03c6 s , decay width difference \u2206\u0393s, and CP violation parameters in the Bs and Bu decays.",
            "paragraph_rank": 0,
            "section_rank": 1
        }
    ],
    "body_text": [
        {
            "text": "Introduction",
            "section_rank": 2
        },
        {
            "text": "The CDF and D\u00d8 experiments have successfully collected data since start of the Run II at the Tevatron Collider in 2001. ",
            "section": "Introduction",
            "paragraph_rank": 1,
            "section_rank": 2
        },
        {
            "text": "The presented results correspond to an integrated luminosity of up to 2.8 fb \u22121 at each experiment. ",
            "section": "Introduction",
            "paragraph_rank": 1,
            "section_rank": 2
        },
        {
            "text": "The large B-meson production cross-section allows enough data to be collected to study the tiny effects of CP-violation in B systems. ",
            "section": "Introduction",
            "paragraph_rank": 1,
            "section_rank": 2
        },
        {
            "text": "In particular, the results described in this paper cover measurements of the mixing phase \u03c6 J/\u03c8\u03c6 s , decay width difference \u2206\u0393 s , semileptonic asymmetry a sl s in the B s system and direct CP violation in the B s and B u systems.",
            "section": "Introduction",
            "paragraph_rank": 1,
            "section_rank": 2
        },
        {
            "text": "A theoretical overview of B s \u2212B s mixing is given in [1,2]. ",
            "section": "Introduction",
            "paragraph_rank": 2,
            "section_rank": 2,
            "ref_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 54,
                    "end": 57,
                    "type": "bibr",
                    "ref_id": "b0",
                    "text": "[1,"
                },
                {
                    "start": 57,
                    "end": 59,
                    "type": "bibr",
                    "ref_id": "b1",
                    "text": "2]"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "text": "Flavour eigenstates of B s meson propagate according to the Schr\u00f6dinger equation:",
            "section": "Introduction",
            "paragraph_rank": 2,
            "section_rank": 2
        },
        {
            "text": "The physical eigenstates |B H and |B L have different masses and lifetimes:",
            "section": "Introduction",
            "paragraph_rank": 3,
            "section_rank": 2
        },
        {
            "text": "where",
            "section": "Introduction",
            "paragraph_rank": 4,
            "section_rank": 2
        },
        {
            "text": "is the CP phase. ",
            "section": "Introduction",
            "paragraph_rank": 5,
            "section_rank": 2
        },
        {
            "text": "The CP phase for the B s system is very small in the Standard Model (SM): \u03c6 SM s \u2248 0.004. ",
            "section": "Introduction",
            "paragraph_rank": 5,
            "section_rank": 2
        },
        {
            "text": "The review [2] predicts that the CP phase \u03c6 s is the most sensitive to the new physics effects. ",
            "section": "Introduction",
            "paragraph_rank": 5,
            "section_rank": 2,
            "ref_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 11,
                    "end": 14,
                    "type": "bibr",
                    "ref_id": "b1",
                    "text": "[2]"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "text": "The semileptonic asymmetry defined as",
            "section": "Introduction",
            "paragraph_rank": 5,
            "section_rank": 2
        },
        {
            "text": "where",
            "section": "Introduction",
            "paragraph_rank": 6,
            "section_rank": 2
        },
        {
            "text": ", is related to the CP phase:",
            "section": "Introduction",
            "paragraph_rank": 7,
            "section_rank": 2
        },
        {
            "text": "Measurements of all four parameters in the equation 6 allow testing of the SM predictions with high sensitivity. ",
            "section": "Introduction",
            "paragraph_rank": 8,
            "section_rank": 2
        },
        {
            "text": "The mixing phase \u03b2 s with the SM prediction",
            "section": "Introduction",
            "paragraph_rank": 8,
            "section_rank": 2
        },
        {
            "text": "02 measured in decays B s \u2192 J/\u03c8\u03c6 is also related to the phase \u03c6 s (see note in [3]). ",
            "section": "Introduction",
            "paragraph_rank": 9,
            "section_rank": 2,
            "ref_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 79,
                    "end": 82,
                    "type": "bibr",
                    "ref_id": "b2",
                    "text": "[3]"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "text": "In paper [4] the notation \u03c6 s = \u22122\u03b2 s is used, but to distinguish this phase from the CP phase \u03c6 s defined above in equation 4 the notation \u03c6 [5] is preferable. ",
            "section": "Introduction",
            "paragraph_rank": 9,
            "section_rank": 2,
            "ref_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 9,
                    "end": 12,
                    "type": "bibr",
                    "ref_id": "b3",
                    "text": "[4]"
                },
                {
                    "start": 142,
                    "end": 145,
                    "type": "bibr",
                    "ref_id": "b4",
                    "text": "[5]"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "text": "The new physics contribution could be described by the phase \u03c6 N P s which modifies the original mixing phases in the following way:",
            "section": "Introduction",
            "paragraph_rank": 9,
            "section_rank": 2
        },
        {
            "text": "The system J/\u03c8 + \u03c6 from B s decay represents an admixture of CP-even and CP-odd states. ",
            "section": "Introduction",
            "paragraph_rank": 10,
            "section_rank": 2
        },
        {
            "text": "Angular analysis could be used to separate the CP components (see figure 1) and measure the lifetime of each component and phase \u03c6 J/\u03c8\u03c6 s [7]. ",
            "section": "Introduction",
            "paragraph_rank": 10,
            "section_rank": 2,
            "ref_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 66,
                    "end": 74,
                    "type": "figure",
                    "ref_id": "fig_0",
                    "text": "figure 1"
                },
                {
                    "start": 138,
                    "end": 141,
                    "type": "bibr",
                    "ref_id": "b6",
                    "text": "[7]"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "text": "Additional information on the initial state flavor of the B s meson helps resolve the sign ambiguity on \u03c6 J/\u03c8\u03c6 s for a given \u2206\u0393 s and improves the precision of results. ",
            "section": "Introduction",
            "paragraph_rank": 10,
            "section_rank": 2
        },
        {
            "text": "The CDF collaboration used the data sample corresponding to 1.7 fb \u22121 (this result was updated recently using 2.8 fb \u22121 data sample [8]) and the D\u00d8 data sample corresponds to 2.8 fb \u22121 . ",
            "section": "Introduction",
            "paragraph_rank": 10,
            "section_rank": 2,
            "ref_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 132,
                    "end": 135,
                    "type": "bibr",
                    "ref_id": "b7",
                    "text": "[8]"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "text": "Constraints on the strong phases \u03b4 i from the B d system allow the sign ambiguity on \u2206\u0393 s to be resolved (see recent theoretical work [9]). ",
            "section": "Introduction",
            "paragraph_rank": 10,
            "section_rank": 2,
            "ref_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 134,
                    "end": 137,
                    "type": "bibr",
                    "ref_id": "b8",
                    "text": "[9]"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "text": "The CDF and D\u00d8 results obtained with different constraints, and compared with the SM prediction are shown in figure 2. ",
            "section": "Introduction",
            "paragraph_rank": 10,
            "section_rank": 2
        },
        {
            "text": "The HFAG combination [5] gives two sets of the numerical results obtained with free phases \u03b4 i :   ",
            "section": "Introduction",
            "paragraph_rank": 10,
            "section_rank": 2,
            "ref_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 21,
                    "end": 24,
                    "type": "bibr",
                    "ref_id": "b4",
                    "text": "[5]"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "text": "\u2206\u0393",
            "section_rank": 3
        },
        {
            "text": "The final state in",
            "section": "\u2206\u0393",
            "paragraph_rank": 11,
            "section_rank": 3
        },
        {
            "text": "s decays is CPeven, although the theoretical uncertainty is not well understood (see for example the discussion in [2]). ",
            "section": "\u2206\u0393",
            "paragraph_rank": 12,
            "section_rank": 3,
            "ref_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 115,
                    "end": 118,
                    "type": "bibr",
                    "ref_id": "b1",
                    "text": "[2]"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "text": "The branching ratio Br",
            "section": "\u2206\u0393",
            "paragraph_rank": 12,
            "section_rank": 3
        },
        {
            "text": "s ) could be used to calculate the decay width difference from the following equation derived in [1]:",
            "section": "\u2206\u0393",
            "paragraph_rank": 13,
            "section_rank": 3,
            "ref_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 97,
                    "end": 100,
                    "type": "bibr",
                    "ref_id": "b0",
                    "text": "[1]"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "text": "The efficient muon triggering system at D\u00d8 provides access to these decays through the muons from semileptonic decays of D s mesons: ",
            "section": "\u2206\u0393",
            "paragraph_rank": 14,
            "section_rank": 3
        },
        {
            "text": "CP violation",
            "section_rank": 4
        },
        {
            "text": "4.1. ",
            "section": "CP violation",
            "paragraph_rank": 15,
            "section_rank": 4
        },
        {
            "text": "B s semileptonic decays [11,12] The SM prediction for the semileptonic asymmetry in B s decays is very small [2]: a s sl = (2.06 \u00b1 0.57) \u2022 10 \u22125 .",
            "section": "CP violation",
            "paragraph_rank": 15,
            "section_rank": 4,
            "ref_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 24,
                    "end": 28,
                    "type": "bibr",
                    "ref_id": "b9",
                    "text": "[11,"
                },
                {
                    "start": 28,
                    "end": 31,
                    "type": "bibr",
                    "text": "12]"
                },
                {
                    "start": 109,
                    "end": 112,
                    "type": "bibr",
                    "ref_id": "b1",
                    "text": "[2]"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "text": "At the Tevatron the semileptonic asymmetry could be measured either from an inclusive di-muon sample, where",
            "section": "CP violation",
            "paragraph_rank": 16,
            "section_rank": 4
        },
        {
            "text": ", or by using the XD s \u00b5 sample. ",
            "section": "CP violation",
            "paragraph_rank": 17,
            "section_rank": 4
        },
        {
            "text": "The first method has very high statistical accuracy, but requires knowledge of asymmetries of other contributing processes in addition to the detector charge asymmetries. ",
            "section": "CP violation",
            "paragraph_rank": 17,
            "section_rank": 4
        },
        {
            "text": "The second method has less statistical power but ensures that the major contribution to the asymmetry comes from the B s decays. ",
            "section": "CP violation",
            "paragraph_rank": 17,
            "section_rank": 4
        },
        {
            "text": "The time-integrated untagged analysis at D\u00d8 used the data sample XD s (\u03c6\u03c0)\u00b5 corresponding to 1.3 fb \u22121 to obtain the result a s sl = 0.0245 \u00b1 0.0193 \u00b1 0.0035 [13] (this analysis was recently updated using a larger data sample, time dependence and initial-state tagging [14]). ",
            "section": "CP violation",
            "paragraph_rank": 17,
            "section_rank": 4,
            "ref_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 158,
                    "end": 162,
                    "type": "bibr",
                    "ref_id": "b10",
                    "text": "[13]"
                },
                {
                    "start": 269,
                    "end": 273,
                    "type": "bibr",
                    "text": "[14]"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "text": "The description of the method used to determine the detector asymmetries at D\u00d8 is given in [15] where the di-muon asymmetry result is presented. ",
            "section": "CP violation",
            "paragraph_rank": 17,
            "section_rank": 4,
            "ref_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 91,
                    "end": 95,
                    "type": "bibr",
                    "ref_id": "b11",
                    "text": "[15]"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "text": "The combination of the two D\u00d8 results is published in [12]: a s sl = 0.0001 \u00b1 0.0090. ",
            "section": "CP violation",
            "paragraph_rank": 17,
            "section_rank": 4
        },
        {
            "text": "The preliminary CDF result obtained using the inclusive di-muon sample is shown in [11]: a s sl = 0.020 \u00b1 0.021 \u00b1 0.018.",
            "section": "CP violation",
            "paragraph_rank": 17,
            "section_rank": 4,
            "ref_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 83,
                    "end": 87,
                    "type": "bibr",
                    "ref_id": "b9",
                    "text": "[11]"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "text": "B s \u2192 K\u03c0 [16]",
            "section_rank": 5
        },
        {
            "text": "The recent measurements of direct CP violation in the B u and B d systems led to the K\u03c0 puzzle (see for example [17]). ",
            "section": "B s \u2192 K\u03c0 [16]",
            "paragraph_rank": 18,
            "section_rank": 5,
            "ref_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 112,
                    "end": 116,
                    "type": "bibr",
                    "ref_id": "b12",
                    "text": "[17]"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "text": "It is therefore important to measure similar signatures in the B s system (see discussion in [18]). ",
            "section": "B s \u2192 K\u03c0 [16]",
            "paragraph_rank": 18,
            "section_rank": 5,
            "ref_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 93,
                    "end": 97,
                    "type": "bibr",
                    "ref_id": "b13",
                    "text": "[18]"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "text": "The impact parameter triggers at CDF are used to collect the hadronic B-decays which are necessary for studies of CP eigenstates. ",
            "section": "B s \u2192 K\u03c0 [16]",
            "paragraph_rank": 18,
            "section_rank": 5
        },
        {
            "text": "Figure 3 shows the invariant mass distribution for 2 body hadronic decays at CDF assuming pion masses for the tracks. ",
            "section": "B s \u2192 K\u03c0 [16]",
            "paragraph_rank": 18,
            "section_rank": 5,
            "ref_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 0,
                    "end": 8,
                    "type": "figure",
                    "ref_id": "fig_5",
                    "text": "Figure 3"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "text": "This sample allowed CDF to produce the only measurement of direct CP violation in the B s system:",
            "section": "B s \u2192 K\u03c0 [16]",
            "paragraph_rank": 18,
            "section_rank": 5
        },
        {
            "text": "NB s \u2192K + \u03c0 \u2212 +N Bs\u2192K \u2212 \u03c0 + = 0.39 \u00b1 0.15(stat.) \u00b1 0.08(syst.). ",
            "section": "B s \u2192 K\u03c0 [16]",
            "paragraph_rank": 19,
            "section_rank": 5
        },
        {
            "text": "This result is in agreement with the theoretical predictions [19].  ",
            "section": "B s \u2192 K\u03c0 [16]",
            "paragraph_rank": 19,
            "section_rank": 5,
            "ref_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 61,
                    "end": 65,
                    "type": "bibr",
                    "ref_id": "b14",
                    "text": "[19]"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "text": "B \u00b1",
            "section_rank": 6
        },
        {
            "text": "CP analysis of the decays B \u00b1 \u2192 D 0 K \u00b1 represents another example of using the impact parameter triggers at CDF. ",
            "section": "B \u00b1",
            "paragraph_rank": 20,
            "section_rank": 6
        },
        {
            "text": "The CP asymmetry is measured in these decays. ",
            "section": "B \u00b1",
            "paragraph_rank": 20,
            "section_rank": 6
        },
        {
            "text": "This asymmetry is relevant for the determination of the CKM angle \u03b3 (see [23,24]). ",
            "section": "B \u00b1",
            "paragraph_rank": 20,
            "section_rank": 6,
            "ref_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 73,
                    "end": 77,
                    "type": "bibr",
                    "ref_id": "b18",
                    "text": "[23,"
                },
                {
                    "start": 77,
                    "end": 80,
                    "type": "bibr",
                    "ref_id": "b19",
                    "text": "24]"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "text": "The D 0 meson decays either to CP eigenstates K + K \u2212 (\u03c0 + \u03c0 \u2212 ), or flavour eigenstate K \u2212 \u03c0 + . ",
            "section": "B \u00b1",
            "paragraph_rank": 20,
            "section_rank": 6
        },
        {
            "text": "The different modes were separated using invariant masses, momentum imbalance, total momentum and dE/dx information. ",
            "section": "B \u00b1",
            "paragraph_rank": 20,
            "section_rank": 6
        },
        {
            "text": "The measured asymmetries agree with the B-factory measurements [25,26] and have competitive precision:",
            "section": "B \u00b1",
            "paragraph_rank": 20,
            "section_rank": 6,
            "ref_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 63,
                    "end": 67,
                    "type": "bibr",
                    "ref_id": "b20",
                    "text": "[25,"
                },
                {
                    "start": 67,
                    "end": 70,
                    "type": "bibr",
                    "ref_id": "b21",
                    "text": "26]"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "text": ".57 \u00b1 0.24(stat.) \u00b1 0.12(syst.).",
            "section": "B \u00b1",
            "paragraph_rank": 21,
            "section_rank": 6
        },
        {
            "text": "B \u00b1 \u2192 J/\u03c8K \u00b1 [20]",
            "section_rank": 7
        },
        {
            "text": "Highly efficient di-muon triggers allow for collection of large J/\u03c8 samples at Tevatron which are competitive with the B-factories in some of the CP violation measurements in B u and B d systems. ",
            "section": "B \u00b1 \u2192 J/\u03c8K \u00b1 [20]",
            "paragraph_rank": 22,
            "section_rank": 7
        },
        {
            "text": "The SM expectation of the direct CP asymmetry in B \u00b1 \u2192 J/\u03c8K \u00b1 decays is small: A J/\u03c8K SM \u223c 0.003 [21]. ",
            "section": "B \u00b1 \u2192 J/\u03c8K \u00b1 [20]",
            "paragraph_rank": 22,
            "section_rank": 7,
            "ref_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 97,
                    "end": 101,
                    "type": "bibr",
                    "ref_id": "b16",
                    "text": "[21]"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "text": "However, the new physics effects (for example a fourth generation) may enhance the asymmetry up to 0.01. ",
            "section": "B \u00b1 \u2192 J/\u03c8K \u00b1 [20]",
            "paragraph_rank": 22,
            "section_rank": 7
        },
        {
            "text": "The D\u00d8 experiment measured this asymmetry to be A J/\u03c8K = +0.0075 \u00b1 0.0061(stat.) \u00b1 0.0027(syst.).",
            "section": "B \u00b1 \u2192 J/\u03c8K \u00b1 [20]",
            "paragraph_rank": 22,
            "section_rank": 7
        },
        {
            "text": "Conclusion",
            "section_rank": 8
        },
        {
            "text": "So far, the Tevatron experiments CDF and D\u00d8 have provided the unique sources of the CP parameters in B s system. ",
            "section": "Conclusion",
            "paragraph_rank": 23,
            "section_rank": 8
        },
        {
            "text": "The complimentary measurements in B u/d systems are not only supporting the B s analyses but also providing results competitive with the B-factories. ",
            "section": "Conclusion",
            "paragraph_rank": 23,
            "section_rank": 8
        },
        {
            "text": "Interestingly though, the CP parameters in the B s system start showing some deviations from the SM predictions in addition to the B u/d puzzles. ",
            "section": "Conclusion",
            "paragraph_rank": 23,
            "section_rank": 8
        },
        {
            "text": "All analyses are statistically limited and the precision will improve in the near future.",
            "section": "Conclusion",
            "paragraph_rank": 23,
            "section_rank": 8
        },
        {
            "text": "The author thanks the organisers of the QCD08 Conference for a very interesting program and the physics analysis representatives from CDF and D\u00d8 for providing results.",
            "section": "Conclusion",
            "paragraph_rank": 24,
            "section_rank": 8,
            "entity_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 80,
                    "end": 87,
                    "type": "software",
                    "rawForm": "program",
                    "resp": "whitelist",
                    "id": "software-simple-w0"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "text": "Figure 1 .",
            "section_rank": 9
        },
        {
            "text": "Figure 1. ",
            "section": "Figure 1 .",
            "paragraph_rank": 25,
            "section_rank": 9
        },
        {
            "text": "The transversity distribution for the signal-enhanced J/\u03c8\u03c6 subsample: non-prompt and signal mass region. ",
            "section": "Figure 1 .",
            "paragraph_rank": 25,
            "section_rank": 9
        },
        {
            "text": "The curves show: the signal contribution, dotted (red); the background, light solid (green); and total, dark solid (blue).",
            "section": "Figure 1 .",
            "paragraph_rank": 25,
            "section_rank": 9
        },
        {
            "text": "Figure 2 .",
            "section_rank": 10
        },
        {
            "text": "Figure 2. ",
            "section": "Figure 2 .",
            "paragraph_rank": 26,
            "section_rank": 10
        },
        {
            "text": "Comparison of the \u03c6 J/\u03c8\u03c6 s results from CDF and D\u00d8 with the SM prediction.",
            "section": "Figure 2 .",
            "paragraph_rank": 26,
            "section_rank": 10
        },
        {
            "text": "\u03b3)\u03c6\u00b5\u03bd). ",
            "paragraph_rank": 27,
            "section_rank": 11
        },
        {
            "text": "Narrow invariant mass peaks from the \u03c6 \u2192 KK decays help to ensure a clean data sample. ",
            "paragraph_rank": 27,
            "section_rank": 11
        },
        {
            "text": "The number of selected D s \u03c6\u00b5 candidates was determined to be N (D s \u03c6\u00b5) = 31.0 \u00b1 9.4 and the resulting branching ratio: Br(B s \u2192 D ( * ) s D ( * ) s ) = 0.042 \u00b1 0.015(stat.) \u00b1 0.017(syst.). ",
            "paragraph_rank": 27,
            "section_rank": 11
        },
        {
            "text": "Assuming no new physics effects (the SM value of \u03c6 SM s \u2248 0.004) one can estimate the decay width difference from equation 7: \u2206\u0393s \u0393s = 0.088 \u00b1 0.030(stat.) \u00b1 0.036(syst.).",
            "paragraph_rank": 27,
            "section_rank": 11
        },
        {
            "text": "Figure 3 .",
            "section_rank": 12
        },
        {
            "text": "Figure 3. ",
            "section": "Figure 3 .",
            "paragraph_rank": 28,
            "section_rank": 12
